column2: VARDESC
Have you had pain in your teeth/toothache because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had discolored teeth or spots on your teeth because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had crooked teeth or spaces between your teeth because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had bad breath because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had bleeding gums because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had difficulty eating foods you would like to eat because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you Had trouble sleeping because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you had difficulty saying certain words because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you had difficulty keeping your teeth clean because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you been unhappy or sad because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have felt worried or anxious because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you avoided smiling or laughing with other children because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you felt that you look different because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you been worried about what other people think about your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you been teased, bullied, or called names by other children because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you missed school for any reason because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you not wanted to speak/read out loud in class because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you been confident because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
Have you felt that you were attractive (good looking)  because of your teeth, mouth, or face?
